				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not have centralized account management configured.

The automated check did not detect SSSD, LDAP, or nslcd integration for centralized account management. Local account management tools are present but centralized lifecycle management is required.

Remediation:
1. Install and configure SSSD for Active Directory integration: apt install sssd sssd-ad
2. Configure /etc/sssd/sssd.conf with domain settings
3. Join the system to the AD domain: realm join DOMAIN.COM
4. Verify: id username@domain.com
5. Alternatively, configure LDAP client: apt install libnss-ldapd

Contact the system administrator to implement centralized account management per organizational policy.

</COMMENTS>
