				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not have automated mechanisms for removing temporary accounts after 72 hours.

Remediation:
1. Set account expiration for temporary accounts: chage -E $(date -d "+3 days" +%Y-%m-%d) USERNAME
2. Set default expiration in /etc/default/useradd: EXPIRE=3 (days)
3. Create a cron job or systemd timer to check and disable expired accounts:
   /etc/cron.daily/cleanup-temp-accounts
4. Verify expiration: chage -l USERNAME
5. Document temporary account procedures in organizational policy

Contact the system administrator to implement automated temporary account lifecycle management.

</COMMENTS>
