				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not enforce account lockout after three consecutive invalid logon attempts.

Remediation:
1. Install pam_faillock (included in libpam-modules on Debian 12)
2. Configure /etc/security/faillock.conf:
   deny = 3
   fail_interval = 900
   unlock_time = 0 (or organization-defined period)
3. Add pam_faillock to PAM stack:
   Edit /etc/pam.d/common-auth to include faillock preauth and authfail
4. Set SSH MaxAuthTries in /etc/ssh/sshd_config: MaxAuthTries 3
5. Restart sshd: systemctl restart sshd
6. Verify: faillock --user testuser

Contact the system administrator to configure account lockout policies per DoD requirements.

</COMMENTS>
