Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The Xen Orchestra host operating system has weak SSH cryptographic algorithms configured that do not meet DoD requirements.

The automated check found one or more of the following deficiencies:
- Weak cipher algorithms enabled (3des-cbc, blowfish-cbc, cast128-cbc, arcfour variants)
- Weak MAC algorithms enabled (hmac-md5, hmac-md5-96, hmac-sha1-96, umac-64)
- Weak key exchange algorithms enabled (diffie-hellman-group1-sha1, group14-sha1, group-exchange-sha1)

Remediation Steps:
1. Edit /etc/ssh/sshd_config
2. Set Ciphers to only approved algorithms: aes256-gcm@openssh.com,aes128-gcm@openssh.com,aes256-ctr,aes192-ctr,aes128-ctr
3. Set MACs to only approved algorithms: hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512,hmac-sha2-256
4. Set KexAlgorithms to: curve25519-sha256,curve25519-sha256@libssh.org,ecdh-sha2-nistp256,ecdh-sha2-nistp384,ecdh-sha2-nistp521,diffie-hellman-group16-sha512,diffie-hellman-group18-sha512
5. Restart SSH: systemctl restart sshd
6. Verify: sshd -T | grep -E 'ciphers|macs|kexalgorithms'

Contact the system administrator to harden SSH configuration per DISA STIG requirements.

</COMMENTS>
