Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system audit configuration does not fully capture event type information in audit records.

The automated check found one or more issues: auditd may not be active, syscall audit rules may not include event type classification, or audit log entries may lack type= fields.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd if missing: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable and start: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add syscall audit rules: auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -k exec_cmds
4. Verify rules loaded: auditctl -l
5. Check log content: ausearch -ts recent | head -50

Ensure all audit records contain event type information per GPOS SRG requirements.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
