[ValidTrueComment]:
The system audit records do not properly contain date/time information or time synchronization is not configured.

The automated check found issues with: auditd not being active, audit log timestamps not in expected epoch format, or system clock not synchronized via NTP/Chrony.

Remediation:
1. Install and enable auditd: apt install auditd &amp;&amp; systemctl enable --now auditd
2. Verify log timestamps: ausearch -ts recent | head -20
3. Configure NTP time sync: apt install chrony &amp;&amp; systemctl enable --now chrony
4. Verify time sync: timedatectl status
5. Confirm timestamps are accurate: date &amp;&amp; ausearch -ts recent -i | head -5

Ensure system clock is synchronized and audit records contain valid timestamps.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

