[ValidTrueComment]:
The system audit records do not contain sufficient location information to establish where events occurred.

The automated check found issues: auditd may not be active, filesystem watch rules may be missing, or audit log entries may lack PATH/CWD records.

Remediation:
1. Enable auditd: systemctl enable --now auditd
2. Add filesystem watch rules for critical paths:
   auditctl -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity
   auditctl -w /etc/shadow -p wa -k identity
   auditctl -w /etc/security/ -p wa -k security_config
3. Make rules persistent in /etc/audit/rules.d/
4. Verify PATH/CWD entries: ausearch -ts recent | grep -E "type=(PATH|CWD)"

Ensure audit rules include filesystem watches for security-relevant paths.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

