Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system audit records do not properly track individual user identities for group account actions.

The automated check found issues: auditd may not be active, UID/AUID tracking rules may be missing, or audit log entries may lack auid= fields for individual identification.

Remediation:
1. Enable auditd: systemctl enable --now auditd
2. Ensure PAM audit module is configured: verify pam_loginuid.so in /etc/pam.d/login and /etc/pam.d/sshd
3. Add identity tracking rules:
   auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -F auid!=unset -k identity_tracking
4. Verify auid tracking: ausearch -ts recent | grep "auid=" | head -10
5. Ensure loginuid is set correctly: cat /proc/self/loginuid

Individual accountability through auid tracking is required for all shared/group accounts.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
