Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system is not fully configured to alert on audit processing failures.

Remediation:
1. Edit /etc/audit/auditd.conf and set:
   space_left_action = SYSLOG
   admin_space_left_action = SINGLE
   action_mail_acct = root
   disk_full_action = HALT
   disk_error_action = HALT
2. Install an MTA: apt install postfix (or sendmail/ssmtp/msmtp)
3. Configure root email alias in /etc/aliases to forward to ISSO/SA
4. Restart auditd: systemctl restart auditd
5. Test alert delivery: logger -p local0.emerg "audit test"

ISSO/SA must receive timely notification of audit processing failures.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
