[ValidTrueComment]:
The system clock is not properly synchronized or audit timestamps are not derived from the system clock.

Remediation:
1. Install time sync: apt install chrony (or systemd-timesyncd)
2. Enable and start: systemctl enable --now chrony
3. Verify sync: timedatectl status (check "System clock synchronized: yes")
4. Verify audit timestamps: tail -5 /var/log/audit/audit.log
5. Confirm epoch format: msg=audit(TIMESTAMP:SERIAL) pattern present
6. Check NTP sources: chronyc sources (or timedatectl timesync-status)

Accurate timestamps are critical for audit trail integrity and forensic analysis.

