[ValidTrueComment]:
Audit information is not adequately protected from unauthorized read access.

Remediation:
1. Set directory permissions: chmod 750 /var/log/audit
2. Set log file permissions: chmod 640 /var/log/audit/audit.log*
3. Set ownership: chown root:root /var/log/audit /var/log/audit/audit.log*
4. Configure auditd.conf: log_group = root
5. Restart auditd: systemctl restart auditd
6. Verify: stat -c "%a %U:%G" /var/log/audit /var/log/audit/audit.log

Only authorized personnel (root/audit group) should have read access to audit data.

