Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not provide complete audit coverage for DoD-defined auditable events.

The automated check found gaps in one or more of the four required categories: security object access, logon/access events, account management, or kernel module operations.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable and start: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add DoD-required rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/:
   - Security objects: -w /etc/passwd -p wa -k identity
   - Logon events: -w /var/log/faillog -p wa -k logins
   - Account mgmt: -w /etc/group -p wa -k identity
   - Kernel modules: -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S init_module -k modules
4. Load rules: augenrules --load
5. Verify coverage: auditctl -l | grep -c "^-"

All four DoD event categories must be covered by audit rules.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
