Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
Audit event selection is not properly restricted to ISSM-authorized personnel.

Remediation:
1. Set audit rules ownership: chown root:root /etc/audit/audit.rules /etc/audit/rules.d/*.rules
2. Restrict audit rules: chmod 640 /etc/audit/audit.rules /etc/audit/rules.d/*.rules
3. Restrict auditd.conf: chmod 640 /etc/audit/auditd.conf; chown root:root /etc/audit/auditd.conf
4. Verify auditctl ownership: chown root:root /usr/sbin/auditctl
5. Document ISSM delegation: Record which personnel are authorized to modify audit rules
6. Restart auditd: systemctl restart auditd

Only the ISSM or ISSM-appointed individuals should modify audit event selections.

</COMMENTS>
