Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found deficiencies in access control enforcement on this Debian 12 system.

Findings:
- No SSH AllowUsers/AllowGroups/DenyUsers/DenyGroups configured
- sudo may not be installed or properly configured
- PAM access control rules may not be active

Remediation Steps:
(1) Configure SSH access restrictions in /etc/ssh/sshd_config:
    AllowGroups sshusers admins
(2) Install and configure sudo: apt install sudo
(3) Add access rules in /etc/security/access.conf:
    + : root : LOCAL
    + : admins : ALL
    - : ALL : ALL
(4) Enable pam_access in /etc/pam.d/common-auth
(5) Restart SSH: systemctl restart ssh

The ISSO/ISSM must verify that access control policies align with organizational requirements.

</COMMENTS>
