Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found non-essential capabilities enabled on this Debian 12 system.

Findings:
- One or more SSH non-essential features are enabled
- Non-essential services may be running
- Non-essential packages may be installed

Remediation Steps:
(1) Disable SSH non-essential features in /etc/ssh/sshd_config:
    X11Forwarding no
    AllowTcpForwarding no
    AllowAgentForwarding no
    PermitTunnel no
    GatewayPorts no
(2) Stop and disable non-essential services:
    systemctl stop avahi-daemon &amp;&amp; systemctl disable avahi-daemon
(3) Remove non-essential packages:
    apt remove telnetd rsh-server ypserv
(4) Restart SSH: systemctl restart ssh

The ISSO/ISSM must verify that only mission-essential capabilities remain enabled.

</COMMENTS>
