				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
MFA for network access to privileged accounts is not deployed. No local PAM MFA modules detected and the XO auth-ldap plugin is not active.

Remediation Options:
Option A  Enable AD/LDAP authentication delegation (Recommended):
(1) Install and configure the XO auth-ldap plugin
(2) Point LDAP configuration to AD domain controllers
(3) Ensure AD enforces MFA for privileged accounts
(4) Verify privileged users authenticate through AD when accessing XO

Option B  Deploy local MFA:
(1) Deploy smartcard infrastructure: apt install opensc pcscd libpam-pkcs11
(2) Configure PAM for MFA in /etc/pam.d/common-auth
(3) Configure SSH: AuthenticationMethods publickey,keyboard-interactive
(4) Enroll all privileged users in MFA

For DoD environments, CAC/PIV with PIN satisfies the two-factor requirement (something you have + something you know).

</COMMENTS>
