[ValidTrueComment]:
Individual authentication before group/shared account access requires verification. No local enforcement detected and the XO auth-ldap plugin is not active.

Remediation Options:
Option A  Enable AD/LDAP authentication delegation (Recommended):
(1) Install and configure the XO auth-ldap plugin
(2) Configure individual AD user authentication for XO access
(3) Map AD users/groups to XO roles (admin, operator, viewer)
(4) Disable local XO account creation to enforce AD-only authentication
(5) Verify all XO access requires individual AD credentials

Option B  Enforce local individual authentication:
(1) Disable direct login to shared accounts: set shell to /usr/sbin/nologin
(2) Require sudo for privileged operations with individual user entries
(3) Ensure su requires authentication (no pam_rootok for non-root)
(4) Log all shared account access through sudo logging
(5) Document procedures requiring individual authentication before shared account usage

</COMMENTS>
