Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not properly disable accounts after 35 days of inactivity.

Remediation:
1. Set system default: useradd -D -f 35
2. Verify /etc/default/useradd shows INACTIVE=35
3. Set for existing accounts: chage -I 35 USERNAME (for each user)
4. Verify per-user settings: chage -l USERNAME (check "Password inactive")
5. For all users: awk -F: '{print $1}' /etc/passwd | xargs -I{} chage -I 35 {}

Contact the system administrator to configure account inactivity lockout per DoD 35-day requirement.

</COMMENTS>
