				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not have adequate mechanisms for emergency account lifecycle management.

Remediation:
1. Create emergency accounts with mandatory expiration: useradd -e $(date -d "+3 days" +%Y-%m-%d) emergency_user
2. Create automated cleanup script in /etc/cron.daily/cleanup-emergency-accounts
3. Configure systemd timer for periodic account expiration checks
4. Document emergency account procedures including creation, authorization, and removal
5. Ensure all emergency accounts have expiration dates set: chage -l USERNAME

Contact the ISSO/ISSM to document emergency account management procedures per organizational policy.

</COMMENTS>
