[ValidTrueComment]:
The system has deficiencies in cryptographic integrity protection for remote access sessions.

Deficiencies found may include:
- Weak SSH MAC algorithms configured (hmac-md5, umac-64, etc.)
- Weak host key algorithms (ssh-dss)
- Insecure remote access services installed (telnet, rsh)

Remediation:
1. Configure strong MACs in /etc/ssh/sshd_config:
   MACs hmac-sha2-512-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-256-etm@openssh.com,hmac-sha2-512,hmac-sha2-256
2. Configure strong host key algorithms:
   HostKeyAlgorithms ssh-ed25519,rsa-sha2-512,rsa-sha2-256
3. Remove insecure services: apt remove telnetd rsh-server
4. Restart SSH: systemctl restart sshd
5. Verify: sshd -T | grep macs

</COMMENTS>
