DOCUMENTATION: Audit records contain information identifying the source of audited events. The auditd system records the source process, UID, GID, terminal, and executable path for all audited events. Systemd journal captures the _COMM, _EXE, _CMDLINE, _PID, and _SYSTEMD_UNIT fields that identify the source of each event. The XO Audit Plugin records the userId, subject name, and action endpoint for application-layer events. Together these provide comprehensive event source identification.

