1. Set permissions on audit tools:
   chmod 755 /usr/sbin/auditctl /usr/sbin/auditd /usr/sbin/aureport
   chmod 755 /usr/sbin/ausearch /usr/sbin/autrace /usr/sbin/augenrules
2. Set ownership: chown root:root /usr/sbin/audit*
3. Verify package integrity: dpkg --verify auditd
4. If package modified, reinstall: apt install --reinstall auditd
5. Verify: stat -c "%a %U:%G" /usr/sbin/audit*

Unauthorized access to audit tools could enable tampering with audit capabilities.

</COMMENTS>
				<SEVERITY_OVERRIDE />
				<SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION />
