				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately prevent nonprivileged users from executing privileged functions.

Deficiencies found may include:
- NOPASSWD sudo rules allowing passwordless privilege escalation
- AppArmor not active or in complain mode
- Additional accounts with UID 0 besides root
- sudo not installed or improperly configured

Remediation:
1. Remove NOPASSWD rules from /etc/sudoers and /etc/sudoers.d/*
2. Enable AppArmor: systemctl enable --now apparmor
3. Set profiles to enforce mode: aa-enforce /etc/apparmor.d/*
4. Remove extra UID 0 accounts: userdel ACCOUNT
5. Review sudo configuration: visudo
6. Verify: apparmor_status, grep NOPASSWD /etc/sudoers /etc/sudoers.d/*

</COMMENTS>
