Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not fully audit the execution of privileged functions.

The automated check found issues: auditd may not be active, execve/SUID audit rules may be missing, or not all SUID/SGID binaries are covered by audit rules.

Remediation:
1. Enable auditd: systemctl enable --now auditd
2. Add privileged execution rules:
   auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -k exec_cmds
   auditctl -a always,exit -F arch=b32 -S execve -k exec_cmds
3. Generate SUID/SGID rules:
   find /usr -perm /6000 -type f 2&gt;/dev/null | while read f; do echo "-w $f -p x -k privileged"; done &gt;&gt; /etc/audit/rules.d/privileged.rules
4. Load rules: augenrules --load
5. Verify: auditctl -l | grep privileged

All SUID/SGID binaries must have corresponding audit rules for privileged execution tracking.

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
