Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 1

[ValidTrueComment]:
Audit enforcement of access restrictions is not fully configured.

Possible findings:
(1) auditd service not active
(2) Insufficient audit rules for permission change syscalls
(3) Access denial events not captured

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd
2. Enable auditd: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add permission change rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/access.rules:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S chmod,fchmod,fchmodat -F auid&gt;=1000 -k perm_mod
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S chown,fchown,fchownat -F auid&gt;=1000 -k perm_mod
4. Add access denial rules:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S open,creat,truncate -F exit=-EACCES -k access
5. Reload rules: augenrules --load

</COMMENTS>
