Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check found that multifactor authentication is not configured for remote privileged access on this Debian 12 system.

Findings:
- SSH AuthenticationMethods not configured for multiple factors
- No PAM MFA modules detected
- Smartcard/PIV packages not installed
- XO auth-ldap plugin not detected (no AD authentication delegation)

Remediation Options:
Option A  Enable AD/LDAP authentication delegation (Recommended):
(1) Install and configure the XO auth-ldap plugin in Xen Orchestra
(2) Configure LDAP URI and Base DN pointing to your AD domain controllers
(3) Ensure AD enforces MFA (CAC/PIV, conditional access, or smart card logon)
(4) Verify users authenticate through AD when accessing XO web UI

Option B  Deploy local MFA on the OS:
(1) Install MFA packages: apt install libpam-google-authenticator
(2) Configure PAM for MFA in /etc/pam.d/sshd
(3) Configure SSH: AuthenticationMethods publickey,keyboard-interactive
(4) For CAC/PIV: apt install opensc libpam-pkcs11 pcscd
(5) Restart SSH: systemctl restart ssh

The ISSO/ISSM must verify MFA implementation uses a separate device factor (CAC, hardware token, or authenticator app).

</COMMENTS>
