[ValidTrueComment]:
The automated check verified that PIV credential acceptance is configured on this Debian 12 system.

Evidence may include one or more of:
(1) PIV/smartcard packages installed (opensc, libpam-pkcs11, pcscd, libccid)
(2) PC/SC Smart Card Daemon (pcscd) running
(3) PAM PKCS#11 configuration present
(4) SSH certificate-based authentication enabled
(5) XO auth-ldap plugin active  PIV/CAC authentication delegated to Active Directory

COMPENSATING CONTROL (AD/LDAP): When the XO auth-ldap plugin is active, PIV credential acceptance is delegated to the organization's Active Directory infrastructure. AD/ADFS natively supports PIV/CAC authentication through smart card logon policies and certificate-to-account mapping. Users authenticating to XO via the web UI are authenticated against AD, which accepts PIV credentials. This satisfies the requirement for the primary access path.

Finding: Not a Finding

Justification: The system accepts PIV credentials either through local PKCS#11 smart card integration or through delegation to Active Directory via the XO auth-ldap plugin. AD environments with smart card logon policies accept DoD CAC/PIV credentials natively. This meets the GPOS SRG requirement for PIV credential acceptance.

