[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not implement NSA-approved FIPS cryptography.

Deficiencies found:
- FIPS mode not enabled in kernel (/proc/sys/crypto/fips_enabled = 0)
- OpenSSL FIPS provider not configured
- Boot parameters missing fips=1

Remediation:
1. Install FIPS packages: apt install libssl3 libgcrypt20
2. Enable FIPS mode: Add fips=1 to kernel boot parameters in /etc/default/grub
3. Update GRUB: update-grub
4. Configure OpenSSL: Enable FIPS provider in /etc/ssl/openssl.cnf
5. Reboot the system
6. Verify: cat /proc/sys/crypto/fips_enabled (should return 1)

Note: Enabling FIPS mode may require Vates/vendor support for Debian 12. See VATES_COMPLIANCE_BLOCKERS.md for details on FIPS compliance gaps.

