				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not implement disk encryption to protect data at rest from unauthorized modification.

No LUKS/dm-crypt encrypted volumes were detected.

Remediation:
1. Install cryptsetup: apt install cryptsetup
2. Encrypt data partitions using LUKS: cryptsetup luksFormat /dev/sdX
3. For new installations, select full disk encryption during Debian installer
4. For existing systems, back up data, encrypt partitions, restore data
5. Verify: lsblk -f (should show crypto_LUKS type)

Note: Encrypting the root filesystem of an existing system requires careful planning and a maintenance window. Consider re-deploying the XO VM with LUKS encryption enabled during installation.

</COMMENTS>
