				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not implement disk encryption to prevent unauthorized disclosure of data at rest.

No LUKS/dm-crypt encrypted volumes were detected. Data on this system could be read if physical media is accessed without authorization.

Remediation:
1. Install cryptsetup: apt install cryptsetup
2. For new deployments: select full disk encryption during Debian installer
3. For existing systems: back up data, encrypt partitions with LUKS, restore data
4. Verify encryption: lsblk -f (should show crypto_LUKS), dmsetup status

See V-203745 remediation for detailed steps.

</COMMENTS>
