				<COMMENTS>Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/01/2026:

Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately audit privileged activities.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable service: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add privileged command rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/privileged.rules:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=4294967295 -k privileged
   -w /usr/bin/sudo -p x -k privileged-sudo
   -w /usr/bin/su -p x -k privileged-su
   -w /usr/bin/passwd -p x -k privileged-passwd
   -w /usr/bin/chsh -p x -k privileged-chsh
   -w /usr/bin/chfn -p x -k privileged-chfn
   -w /usr/bin/newgrp -p x -k privileged-newgrp
4. Reload rules: augenrules --load
5. Verify: auditctl -l | grep privileged

Alternative Compensating Control: If auditd installation is not feasible, enable the XO Audit Plugin (Settings &gt; Plugins &gt; audit) which provides application-layer audit records with hash chain integrity verification. The plugin records user actions, login events, permission changes, and configuration modifications. Ensure the API token is configured at /etc/xo-server/stig/api-token for automated scanning. See: https://docs.xen-orchestra.com/users#audit-log

</COMMENTS>
