[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately audit direct access to the information system.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable service: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Configure PAM session modules in /etc/pam.d/common-session:
   session required pam_loginuid.so
   session optional pam_lastlog.so showfailed
4. Add login tracking rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/logins.rules:
   -w /var/log/wtmp -p wa -k logins
   -w /var/log/btmp -p wa -k logins
   -w /var/run/utmp -p wa -k logins
5. Reload: augenrules --load
6. Verify: ausearch -m USER_LOGIN,LOGIN,USER_START -ts recent

