Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately audit kernel module operations and/or program initiations.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable service: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add kernel module rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/modules.rules:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S init_module,finit_module,delete_module -k modules
   -w /usr/sbin/insmod -p x -k modules
   -w /usr/sbin/rmmod -p x -k modules
   -w /usr/sbin/modprobe -p x -k modules
4. Add program initiation rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/privileged.rules:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=4294967295 -k execpriv
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -F euid=0 -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=4294967295 -k execpriv
5. Reload: augenrules --load
6. Verify: auditctl -l | grep -E "modules|execpriv"

</COMMENTS>
