[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not implement NIST FIPS-validated cryptography.

FIPS mode is not enabled. Cryptographic operations may use non-validated algorithms.

Remediation:
1. Enable FIPS kernel mode: Add fips=1 to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX in /etc/default/grub
2. Update GRUB: update-grub
3. Configure OpenSSL FIPS provider in /etc/ssl/openssl.cnf
4. Reboot the system
5. Verify: cat /proc/sys/crypto/fips_enabled (should return 1)
6. Verify OpenSSL: openssl list -providers (should show fips provider)

Note: Debian 12 FIPS enablement may require additional Vates vendor support. See VATES_COMPLIANCE_BLOCKERS.md.

