Answer File: /tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XO_v5.x_GPOS_Debian12_AnswerFile.xml
Key Name: XO
Index: 2

[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately off-load audit data.

Remediation:
1. For real-time off-loading (interconnected systems), configure rsyslog:
   Edit /etc/rsyslog.conf or create /etc/rsyslog.d/remote.conf:
   *.* @@syslog-server.example.com:514
2. Restart rsyslog: systemctl restart rsyslog
3. Alternatively, configure systemd-journal-upload:
   apt install systemd-journal-remote
   Edit /etc/systemd/journal-upload.conf with remote URL
   systemctl enable --now systemd-journal-upload
4. For standalone systems, ensure weekly logrotate:
   Verify /etc/logrotate.d/auditd exists with weekly rotation
5. Configure audisp-remote for audit-specific forwarding:
   Edit /etc/audit/audisp-remote.conf with remote server
6. Verify: logger -p auth.info "test" then check remote server

</COMMENTS>
