[ValidTrueComment]:
The system does not adequately monitor maintenance tool execution with increased privilege.

Remediation:
1. Install auditd: apt install auditd audispd-plugins
2. Enable service: systemctl enable --now auditd
3. Add maintenance tool rules to /etc/audit/rules.d/maintenance.rules:
   -w /usr/sbin/fdisk -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/parted -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/mkfs -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/fsck -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/debugfs -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/bin/mount -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/bin/umount -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/iptables -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/sbin/tcpdump -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/bin/strace -p x -k maintenance
   -w /usr/bin/gdb -p x -k maintenance
4. Add privileged execution monitoring:
   -a always,exit -F arch=b64 -S execve -F euid=0 -F auid&gt;=1000 -F auid!=4294967295 -k maintenance-elevated
5. Reload: augenrules --load
6. Verify: auditctl -l | grep maintenance

